org.alienideology.jcord.handle.message

Class MessageProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.alienideology.jcord.handle.message.MessageProcessor

  • public class MessageProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
    MessageProcessor - The processor of a message. This can process the whole message, or act like a reader with a cursor.
    Author:
    AlienIdeology

        public boolean hasNextMarkdowns(IMessage.Markdown... markdowns)
        Check if the remaining content contains the markdowns combined. For example, IMessage.Markdown.STRIKEOUT combined with IMessage.Markdown.ITALICS would result in ~~*.
        Parameters:
        markdowns - The markdowns to check with.
        Returns:
        True if the remaining content contains the markdowns.

      • getNextMarkdowns

        public MessageProcessor.Token getNextMarkdowns(IMessage.Markdown... markdowns)
        Get the next content that has the markdowns. For example, getting a content such as ~~*Strike and italics!*~~ requires to pass IMessage.Markdown.ITALICS and IMessage.Markdown.STRIKEOUT in the parameter.
        Parameters:
        markdowns - The markdowns to get.
        Returns:
        The content that has the markdownds surrounding it.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If there is no characters remain.

      • getNextMention

        public MessageProcessor.GenericToken<java.lang.String> getNextMention()
        Get the next mention, can be any kind of mention. Note that this MessageProcessor.GenericToken would use String as its generic type, and the string would be mentioned ID.
        Returns:
        The next mention, with the mentioned object as the String ID.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If there is no mentions remain.

      • getNextUserMention

        public MessageProcessor.GenericToken<IUser> getNextUserMention()
        Get the next user mention. Note that user mention is different from member mention. Used mention is in <@ID> format, while member mention is in <@!ID> format.
        Returns:
        The next user mention.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If there is no user mention remain.

      • getNextMemberMention

        public MessageProcessor.GenericToken<IMember> getNextMemberMention()
        Get the next member mention. Member mentions should show nickname, and it only appears in Guild.
        Returns:
        The next member mention.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If there is no member mention remain.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If the message is not from a guild.

      • getProcessedContent

        public java.lang.String getProcessedContent(boolean noMention,
                                            boolean noMarkdown)
        Process the original content of this message.
        Parameters:
        noMention - Should process mention or not.
        Original: <@ID>
        Processed: @NickName/Username#Discriminator X
        noMarkdown - Should include markdown or not.
        Original: **```java\n\nhi```**
        Processed: hi
        Returns:
        The message processed.
